    "created_at": "2015-02-05T22:29:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-02-05T22:29:54Z",
    "body": "If you tell the compiler explicitely to use an `u32`, it will be satisfied:\n\n```\nlet i : u32 = 1 & 0xFFFF0000;\n```\n\nI can't find the exact rules written down atm, but if you don't tell the compiler about a type it will use some default, in this case `i32`\n\nEdit: aaaaand @bluss was faster\u2026\n",
